## Frontend-Specific Rules

### Component Design
- Follow the project's component architecture (atomic design, feature-based, etc.)
- Keep components focused — one responsibility per component
- Separate presentation from logic
- Use the project's established patterns for state management

### Styling
- Follow the project's CSS methodology (CSS Modules, Tailwind, styled-components, etc.)
- Use design tokens / theme variables for colors, spacing, typography
- Ensure responsive design for all new components

### API Integration
- Use the established API client (not raw fetch/axios)
- Handle loading, error, and empty states
- Don't hardcode API URLs — use environment configuration

### Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Add ARIA labels where needed
- Ensure keyboard navigation works
- Test with screen readers for critical flows

### Testing
- Unit tests for utility functions and hooks
- Component tests for interactive components
- E2e tests for critical user flows
- Test both happy path and error states

### Performance
- Lazy-load routes and heavy components
- Optimize images and assets
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders
- Use appropriate caching strategies

